oppressed the Shia majority.

00:17:11.050 --> 00:17:15.730
When we came in, we got
rid of Saddam Hussein.

00:17:15.730 --> 00:17:19.960
We started a
de-Ba'athification program,

00:17:19.960 --> 00:17:23.090
The Ba'ath Party was the sort of
nationalist party under Saddam

00:17:23.090 --> 00:17:23.589
Hussein.

00:17:23.589 --> 00:17:27.760
So he purged the military,
the schools, the universities,

00:17:27.760 --> 00:17:29.660
right down to very
low-level jobs.

00:17:29.660 --> 00:17:31.060
He purge them of all Ba'athists.

00:17:31.060 --> 00:17:33.460
Of course a lot of those
people were perfectly decent

00:17:33.460 --> 00:17:36.100
people who were stuck in a
system where you had to be--

00:17:36.100 --> 00:17:38.680
like under communism
in Eastern Europe,

00:17:38.680 --> 00:17:40.460
you had to be part of
the Communist Party

00:17:40.460 --> 00:17:43.150
in order to even get a
job sweeping the streets.

00:17:43.150 --> 00:17:45.250
Being in the party
doesn't mean anything.

00:17:45.250 --> 00:17:47.800
But we purged all those
people and basically created

00:17:47.800 --> 00:17:50.560
an unemployed and
very bitter population

00:17:50.560 --> 00:17:53.100
who were then oppressed--

00:17:53.100 --> 00:17:55.930
I mean oppressed, murdered,
rounded up, tortured,

00:17:55.930 --> 00:17:58.210
killed, murdered by
the Shia government

00:17:58.210 --> 00:18:01.120
that we put into
power in Baghdad.

00:18:01.120 --> 00:18:06.760
Oddly, the Shia government had
of course very strong relations

00:18:06.760 --> 00:18:09.160
with the Shia government
in Iran who's our enemy.

00:18:09.160 --> 00:18:11.560
So no matter what we
did we were creating

00:18:11.560 --> 00:18:14.640
a contradiction in
our policies, almost

00:18:14.640 --> 00:18:16.570
sort of brilliantly
contradictory policy.

00:18:16.570 --> 00:18:18.070
It would be hard
to actually set out

00:18:18.070 --> 00:18:22.060
to be as contradictory
as we were.

00:18:22.060 --> 00:18:26.200
So a lot of these
disenfranchised Ba'ath Party

00:18:26.200 --> 00:18:30.610
leaders and generals and
officers and party leaders

00:18:30.610 --> 00:18:36.220
and all that eventually
started the Sunni insurgency,

00:18:36.220 --> 00:18:38.731
partly to protect the Sunni
population from the Shia who

00:18:38.731 --> 00:18:39.730
were beating up on them.

00:18:39.730 --> 00:18:45.730
And eventually
when President Bush

00:18:45.730 --> 00:18:48.310
started negotiating a
US withdrawal from Iraq

00:18:48.310 --> 00:18:50.280
and then handed that
off to Barack Obama, who

00:18:50.280 --> 00:18:57.010
sort of finished the job, in
the vacuum of our withdrawal,

00:18:57.010 --> 00:19:00.700
the Shia government--
the Shia forces sort of

00:19:00.700 --> 00:19:04.600
had free reign to really
abuse the Sunni population.

00:19:04.600 --> 00:19:08.650
And at that moment, ISIS was
formed as a civil defense force

00:19:08.650 --> 00:19:10.600
to protect the Sunni population.

00:19:10.600 --> 00:19:14.650
And what they offered
