a sort of broad moral failure

00:25:19.840 --> 00:25:22.720
by the population that they
somehow like violence and can't

00:25:22.720 --> 00:25:25.670
keep themselves from
killing each other.

00:25:25.670 --> 00:25:27.184
That's just not how
civil wars work.

00:25:27.184 --> 00:25:28.850
That's not how it
worked in our country.

00:25:28.850 --> 00:25:30.790
Everyone forgets, we
had a civil war too.

00:25:30.790 --> 00:25:33.940
That's not how it worked in
our country in the 1860s.

00:25:33.940 --> 00:25:36.400
It's not how it works.

00:25:36.400 --> 00:25:39.190
The vast majority of people
are good, decent people

00:25:39.190 --> 00:25:41.560
who don't want to be
killing their neighbors.

00:25:41.560 --> 00:25:45.250
It doesn't take very
many psychopaths

00:25:45.250 --> 00:25:49.390
and nationalists and
power-hungry politicians

00:25:49.390 --> 00:25:51.302
to tip a country into civil war.

00:25:51.302 --> 00:25:52.510
It really doesn't take a lot.

00:25:55.980 --> 00:25:58.890
Likewise in street
demonstrations,

00:25:58.890 --> 00:26:01.310
it doesn't take a lot
of sort of Molotov

00:26:01.310 --> 00:26:03.050
cocktail-throwing
anarchists to turn

00:26:03.050 --> 00:26:06.120
a completely reasonable street
demonstration into a riot.

00:26:06.120 --> 00:26:08.810
It really doesn't take a lot.

00:26:08.810 --> 00:26:12.190
And so I wanted
people to understand

00:26:12.190 --> 00:26:14.946
that the people of Syria or
Bosnia or wherever it is,

00:26:14.946 --> 00:26:16.070
they're just decent people.

00:26:16.070 --> 00:26:17.970
They're people exactly like us.

00:26:17.970 --> 00:26:19.970
And when they flee
with their children,

00:26:19.970 --> 00:26:21.560
they're not trying
to take advantage

00:26:21.560 --> 00:26:24.350
of the bounty of
the West and take

00:26:24.350 --> 00:26:26.240
advantage of our generosity.

00:26:26.240 --> 00:26:29.050
Fleeing their country is
incredibly scary and dangerous.

00:26:29.050 --> 00:26:31.010
It's the last thing any
reasonable person would

00:26:31.010 --> 00:26:32.330
want to do with their children.

00:26:32.330 --> 00:26:34.413
And yet they're doing it
because they know if they

00:26:34.413 --> 00:26:36.100
don't, they're going to die.

00:26:36.100 --> 00:26:39.740
That's what an immigrant
refugee population is.

00:26:39.740 --> 00:26:42.117
And the other
thing I wanted to--

00:26:42.117 --> 00:26:44.075
there are two other things
I wanted to explain.

00:26:46.925 --> 00:26:51.160
First of all, some
of this came out of--

00:26:51.160 --> 00:26:52.450
some of it we can't control.

00:26:52.450 --> 00:26:56.320
The countries have internal
dynamics of civil wars.

00:26:56.320 --> 00:26:57.534
We can't play god.

00:26:57.534 --> 00:26:59.200
Not everything that
happens in the world

00:26:59.200 --> 00:27:03.330
is because we did or
didn't do something.

00:27:03.330 --> 00:27:10.860
But I have to say, our
invasion of Iraq in 2003

00:27:10.860 --> 00:27:13.800
introduced in a huge amount
of instability and violence

00:27:13.800 --> 00:27:16.260
and death into that
part of the world.

00:27:16.260 --> 00:27:18.900
I'm not defending the
Saddam Hussein regime.

00:27:18.900 --> 00:27:22.910
Of course he was
unspeakably evil.

00:27:22.910 --> 00:27:26.310
But just for the
purposes of history,

00:27:26.310 --> 00:27:29.790
we killed something
like 100,000 civilians.

00:27:29.790 --> 00:27:32.910
We introduced
violence as a norm,

00:27:32.910 --> 00:27:37.200
a new norm in Iraqi society, and
made some incredible blunders,

00:27:37.200 --> 00:27:39.150
like de-Ba'athification.

00:27:39.150 --> 00:27:43.929
And when you traumatize
a society like that,

00:27:43.929 --> 00:27:45.220
it's like traumatizing a child.

00:27:45.220 --> 00:27:47.080
It will act badly.

00:27:47.080 --> 00:27:52.000
I mean trauma produces a
result, not a good one.

00:27:57.410 --> 00:27:58.970
And then the
withdrawal-- then if you

00:27:58.970 --> 00:28:00.553
invade a country and
kind of break it,

00:28:00.553 --> 00:28:02.090
then you kind of
should stay there.

00:28:02.090 --> 00:28:04.130
And we didn't do that either.

00:28:04.130 --> 00:28:07.332
I mean in Afghanistan in the
'80s, we armed the Afghans

00:28:07.332 --> 00:28:09.290
to the teeth so they
could fight the Russians--

00:28:09.290 --> 00:28:11.870
which is arguably the
right thing to do--

00:28:11.870 --> 00:28:13.950
spent a huge amount of
money giving them weapons.

00:28:13.950 --> 00:28:16.046
And when the Russians
pulled out, what did we do?

00:28:16.046 --> 00:28:17.420
We didn't care
about the Afghans.

00:28:17.420 --> 00:28:18.650
We pulled out.

00:28:18.650 --> 00:28:21.590
We didn't stay to build schools
and build bridges and help.

00:28:21.590 --> 00:28:23.655
No, all we were doing,
all we were interested in

00:28:23.655 --> 00:28:24.530
was killing Russians.

00:28:24.530 --> 00:28:27.140
We actually didn't care
about the Afghans, at least

00:28:27.140 --> 00:28:30.890
not judging by the money
allocated by this nation

00:28:30.890 --> 00:28:32.510
afterwards.

00:28:32.510 --> 00:28:35.450
So I wanted to make
the point that we

00:28:35.450 --> 00:28:38.840
can be judgmental and whatever
about those crazy people

00:28:38.840 --> 00:28:40.700
over there that have
their crazy civil war.

00:28:40.700 --> 00:28:42.350
We are part of it.

00:28:42.350 --> 00:28:46.230
And America has done enormously
good things in the world too,

00:28:46.230 --> 00:28:48.710
including stopping fascism
during World War II.

00:28:48.710 --> 00:28:51.860
My father grew up in Europe.

00:28:51.860 --> 00:28:54.590
He's alive because-- I mean
his homeland survived--

00:28:54.590 --> 00:28:57.560
France survived because of us.

00:28:57.560 --> 00:29:00.920
I mean, he made that very
clear to me when I was young.

00:29:00.920 --> 00:29:05.030
So we're an enormous power
for good in the world as well.

00:29:05.030 --> 00:29:06.740
But we need to own our mistakes.

00:29:06.740 --> 00:29:11.960
And I would like to propose Iraq
was a mistake, in that sense.

00:29:11.960 --> 00:29:17.390
And finally, the public
use of violence by ISIS--

00:29:17.390 --> 00:29:19.580
I mean taking people
into the town square,

00:29:19.580 --> 00:29:22.520
pouring gasoline over them,
and burning them alive,

00:29:22.520 --> 00:29:27.160
putting them in steel cages,
groups of men in steel cages,

00:29:27.160 --> 00:29:29.470
and then dangling them over
a swimming pool by a crane

00:29:29.470 --> 00:29:31.570
and then slowly dropping
them into the water

00:29:31.570 --> 00:29:34.810
and watching them drown, with
underwater cameras to record

00:29:34.810 --> 00:29:39.280
it, that is pure evil, right?

00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:43.390
It's an evil of the sort that
is absolutely unacceptable

00:29:43.390 --> 00:29:47.189
and I'm glad they're being
eradicated from the planet,

00:29:47.189 --> 00:29:49.480
but it's the kind of evil
that every society, including

00:29:49.480 --> 00:29:51.460
our own, has indulged in.

00:29:51.460 --> 00:29:53.440
I mean people commit
public violence in order

00:29:53.440 --> 00:29:55.300
to intimidate other people.

00:29:55.300 --> 00:29:57.760
And you don't have to go very
far back in American history

00:29:57.760 --> 00:30:00.140
to find public violence.

00:30:00.140 --> 00:30:02.170
I mean the lynchings of
black men in the South,

00:30:02.170 --> 00:30:05.410
I mean those men
could have been easily

00:30:05.410 --> 00:30:07.690
killed quietly in the
dead of night and buried.

00:30:07.690 --> 00:30:09.850
That's how people
commit murder, right?

00:30:09.850 --> 00:30:11.492
They do it quietly and secretly.

00:30:11.492 --> 00:30:13.450
That's not what happened
in the American South.

00:30:13.450 --> 00:30:17.950
The murders were done in
an intentionally cruel way

00:30:17.950 --> 00:30:19.450
in the middle of town.

00:30:19.450 --> 00:30:21.658
I mean, there were ministers
who would let church out

00:30:21.658 --> 00:30:25.540
early so that the congregation
wouldn't miss the lynching.

00:30:25.540 --> 00:30:27.640
That's an attempt to
intimidate the population

00:30:27.640 --> 00:30:28.780
just like ISIS was doing.

00:30:28.780 --> 00:30:30.670
So one of the points
I wanted to make

00:30:30.670 --> 00:30:33.610
is that ISIS must be
condemned, but in the context

00:30:33.610 --> 00:30:37.720
of acknowledging that
every society has

00:30:37.720 --> 00:30:39.860
used that kind of violence.

00:30:39.860 --> 00:30:42.820
And we need to
acknowledge that dark--

00:30:42.820 --> 00:30:45.580
in condemning the
dark side of ISIS,

00:30:45.580 --> 00:30:47.830
in the same moment
we have to actually,

00:30:47.830 --> 00:30:50.530
to be intellectually honest,
acknowledge the dark side

00:30:50.530 --> 00:30:52.830
that we're capable of, and
thank God have transcended.

00:30:52.830 --> 00:30:54.790
But we can't forget that.

00:30:54.790 --> 00:30:58.434
We can't be too sanctimonious
that they're somehow inherently

00:30:58.434 --> 00:30:59.350
different than we are.

00:30:59.350 --> 00:31:01.141
You go back two
generations in this country

00:31:01.141 --> 00:31:02.439
and they're really not.

00:31:02.439 --> 00:31:03.980
JORDAN THIBODEAU:
Now the documentary

00:31:03.980 --> 00:31:08.480
showed how a person got
radicalized and joined ISIS.

00:31:08.480 --> 00:31:11.540
I guess there is a
theory that people

00:31:11.540 --> 00:31:13.970
join these groups because of
lack of economic opportunity.

00:31:13.970 --> 00:31:15.928
And some other people
think, no, it's not that.

00:31:15.928 --> 00:31:17.597
It's for other causes.

00:31:17.597 --> 00:31:18.680
Where do you land on that?

00:31:20.655 --> 00:31:22.280
SEBASTIAN JUNGER:
There's a whole range

00:31:22.280 --> 00:31:23.780
of reasons to join ISIS.

00:31:23.780 --> 00:31:27.140
If you're Syrian and ISIS rolls
into your hometown in pickup

00:31:27.140 --> 00:31:29.720
trucks, a really compelling
reason to join ISIS is that

00:31:29.720 --> 00:31:31.030
they'll kill you if you don't.

00:31:31.030 --> 00:31:35.480
So there's that to some
sort of economic opportunity

00:31:35.480 --> 00:31:37.970
in those areas for
disenfranchised people

00:31:37.970 --> 00:31:41.480
that feel like they need to join
the winning team to survive.

00:31:44.580 --> 00:31:47.180
And then if you move to
the European population,

00:31:47.180 --> 00:31:48.140
why would--

00:31:48.140 --> 00:31:50.540
I mean, it was mostly
middle-class kids

00:31:50.540 --> 00:31:51.620
that joined ISIS.

00:31:51.620 --> 00:31:57.590
Why would a middle class kid
in Europe of Arab descent--

00:31:57.590 --> 00:32:00.080
but not an immigrant,
not a refugee,

00:32:00.080 --> 00:32:04.460
someone who was born in France
or in England of Arab descent,

00:32:04.460 --> 00:32:08.300
middle-class kid who's in school
and university, whatever--

00:32:08.300 --> 00:32:09.620
why would they join ISIS?

00:32:09.620 --> 00:32:12.007
They are not economically
desperate people actually.

00:32:12.007 --> 00:32:14.090
That's not the kind of
people who would join ISIS.

00:32:14.090 --> 00:32:15.447
They're too busy working.

00:32:15.447 --> 00:32:17.780
They're too busy trying to
work and with their families.

00:32:17.780 --> 00:32:19.760
It's really middle-class kids.

00:32:19.760 --> 00:32:23.370
And teenagers are particularly
vulnerable to sort

00:32:23.370 --> 00:32:24.470
of utopian visions.

00:32:24.470 --> 00:32:28.970
And ISIS wasn't trying to
lure them in to their movement

00:32:28.970 --> 00:32:31.610
by showing beheading
videos, because then you

00:32:31.610 --> 00:32:32.990
only get the psychopaths.

00:32:32.990 --> 00:32:35.214
And psychopaths can be
useful, but you can't have

00:32:35.214 --> 00:32:36.380
a whole army of psychopaths.

00:32:36.380 --> 00:32:37.754
There just aren't
enough of them.

00:32:37.754 --> 00:32:41.960
So what they did to lure
people is to give them

00:32:41.960 --> 00:32:43.250
a vision of a utopia.

00:32:43.250 --> 00:32:48.320
And so they had these videos
of incredibly high production

00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:52.490
values showing a family
in ISIS territory

00:32:52.490 --> 00:32:55.220
having a picnic by a
lake, things like that,

00:32:55.220 --> 00:32:58.610
just this sort of
utopian, idealized vision

00:32:58.610 --> 00:33:03.740
of life inside the caliphate.

00:33:03.740 --> 00:33:06.470
And also just the whole
idea of the caliphate

00:33:06.470 --> 00:33:08.360
is finally standing
up to the West

00:33:08.360 --> 00:33:13.190
and reclaiming this very
real, sort of historical,

00:33:13.190 --> 00:33:17.810
sort of lost golden
age of Islam,

00:33:17.810 --> 00:33:19.910
and this sort of
very real dignity

00:33:19.910 --> 00:33:23.240
that the Arab world had
in regard to the West.

00:33:23.240 --> 00:33:24.830
That had been lost.

00:33:24.830 --> 00:33:27.040
And they're very conscious
that it's been lost.

00:33:27.040 --> 00:33:30.140
And totally reasonable,
they want to reclaim it.

00:33:30.140 --> 00:33:31.610
We would too.

00:33:31.610 --> 00:33:33.290
And so what they
do is these videos

00:33:33.290 --> 00:33:35.120
that they put out
there were showing

00:33:35.120 --> 00:33:38.930
in a very glowing sort
of light this utopia

00:33:38.930 --> 00:33:40.187
that you can come join.

00:33:40.187 --> 00:33:42.770
And also, young people want to
be something bigger themselves,

00:33:42.770 --> 00:33:45.954
greater than themselves.

00:33:45.954 --> 00:33:47.870
There's a great band,
Queens of the Stone Age,

00:33:47.870 --> 00:33:49.670
and they have lyrics
to one of their--

00:33:49.670 --> 00:33:51.320
I can't remember the
name of the song.

00:33:51.320 --> 00:33:53.990
The lyric is, "She
wanted something

00:33:53.990 --> 00:33:56.210
to die for to make it
beautiful to live."

00:33:56.210 --> 00:33:56.870
That's ISIS.

00:33:56.870 --> 00:33:58.244
I mean that's the
appeal of ISIS.

00:33:58.244 --> 00:34:00.200
That's the appeal
of, in the 1930s,

00:34:00.200 --> 00:34:04.760
going over and fighting
the Spanish Civil War.

00:34:04.760 --> 00:34:07.989
And that's exactly what's going
on with those kids in Europe.

00:34:07.989 --> 00:34:09.530
And then they get
over there and they

00:34:09.530 --> 00:34:13.460
realize it's a
complete lie and it's

00:34:13.460 --> 00:34:15.690
a horribly abusive and
depraved organization.

00:34:15.690 --> 00:34:16.699
But then it's too late.

00:34:16.699 --> 00:34:20.559
Then they're basically stuck.

00:34:20.559 --> 00:34:23.100
JORDAN THIBODEAU: Now the US is
